# Usage Guide

## Setup
1. Create and activate virtual environment:
   ```bash
   python -m venv venv
   venv\Scripts\activate      # on Windows
   source venv/bin/activate   # on Linux/macOS
   ```

2. Install dependencies:
   ```bash
   pip install -r requirements.txt
   ```

3. Prepare input files in `data/` folder:
   - `data/private_key.txt`: Ethereum private keys (one per line)
   - `data/proxy.txt`: Proxies in `user:pass@ip:port` format (one per line)
   - `data/twitter_token.txt`: Twitter auth tokens (one per line)
   - `data/invite.txt`: Invitation codes (one per line)

## Running the CLI
Execute [main.py](mdc:main.py) to access the interactive menu:
```bash
python main.py
```

### Menu Options
1. Registration - Register Ethereum wallets (using private keys and invite codes)
2. Twitter Binding - Connect Twitter accounts to registered wallets
3. Mining Scheduler - Start the automated mining job scheduler
4. Exit - Exit the program

### Configuration
- Edit core settings in [config.py](mdc:config.py)
- Override settings using [settings.yaml](mdc:settings.yaml):
  ```yaml
  start_delay_sec: 10    # Delay between operations
  concurrency: 3         # Max concurrent mining jobs
  ```
